{"type":"message","id":"a857bacc","parentId":"1c20b185","timestamp":"2026-05-18T06:41:28.754Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"I found it! At the very end of the config, there's:\n\n```json\n\"capability-evolver\": {\n  \"enabled\": true\n}\n```\n\nSo the capability-evolver plugin is still **enabled** in the config! Even though MEMORY.md says \"Capability Evolver — 已卸载，不再使用\", the config still has it enabled. This is likely why the user is still receiving those messages.\n\nI need to disable it by setting `enabled: false` in the config. Let me do that using the gateway config.patch tool.\n\nActually wait - looking at the structure, this is inside `plugins.entries`. So to disable it, I need to patch `plugins.entries.capability-evolver.enabled` to `false`.\n\nLet me do that.","thinkingSignature":"13fe9a3da4326b3ae2c56485e6d7d9f02c2baabdffe0d067e51df435be2bb544"},{"type":"text","text":"找到问题了！配置里 `capability-evolver` 仍然是 `enabled: true`：\n\n```json\n\"capability-evolver\": {\n  \"enabled\": true\n}\n```\n\n虽然 MEMORY.md 记了\"已卸载\"，但配置里没改。我现在把它关掉：\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_sgzu2ngjhn7y_1","name":"gateway","arguments":{"action":"config.patch","path":"plugins.entries.capability-evolver","raw":"{\"enabled\": false}","note":"已关闭 capability-evolver，不再发送相关消息"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":8636,"output":283,"cacheRead":26290,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":35209,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1779086480825,"responseId":"0659e791db2cbd2df14969549978f687"}}
