{"type":"message","id":"db27f511","parentId":"57ab69d2","timestamp":"2026-05-18T06:42:04.954Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The gateway keeps saying \"device identity required\" even though the status shows it's running. This is strange. Let me try a different approach - maybe I need to directly edit the JSON config file and then restart the gateway.\n\nActually, looking at the error message again: \"gateway closed (1008): device identity required\". This might be an issue with how the gateway tool connects to the gateway. The gateway is running locally on loopback, and the config looks correct. But the tool is getting a 1008 error which typically means \"Gateway closed\" with some WebSocket issue.\n\nLet me try editing the openclaw.json file directly with exec, and then do a manual restart if needed.","thinkingSignature":"bb1f44b97e158131460c1c004720e0ebede772e8f8581aebc06daffa453c7196"},{"type":"text","text":"The gateway tool keeps failing. Let me try directly editing the config file and then restarting:\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_s8f09w1aegzu_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"sed -i 's/\"capability-evolver\": {*\"enabled\": true*\"}/\"capability-evolver\": { \"enabled\": false }/g' ~/.openclaw/openclaw.json && echo \"done\"","timeout":5}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":10010,"output":235,"cacheRead":26290,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":36535,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1779086516725,"responseId":"0659e7b5aa1f54d50908671e62dca67e"}}
