{"type":"message","id":"c7b8cb30","parentId":"41b5bbbb","timestamp":"2026-05-18T06:42:29.734Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Hmm, it says \"capability-evolver not found in plugins.entries\". But earlier when I ran `cat ~/.openclaw/openclaw.json | python3 -c \"import json,sys; d=json.load(sys.stdin); print(json.dumps(d, indent=2))\" 2>/dev/null | tail -100` I saw it at the end of the file:\n\n```json\n\"capability-evolver\": {\n  \"enabled\": true\n}\n```\n\nBut that was AFTER all the plugin entries. Let me check the actual structure of the config again. Maybe the capability-evolver is not inside plugins.entries but somewhere else in the config.\n\nLet me look at the full config structure again.","thinkingSignature":"405c991011d5622fbf6a2d47c90007898fceeee89a142c88f0db06729579935b"},{"type":"text","text":"Interesting - it says \"not found\" in plugins.entries. Let me check where exactly the capability-evolver section is in the config:\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_qj0zj555gg6p_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"python3 -c \"\nimport json\nwith open('/home/halei/.openclaw/openclaw.json', 'r') as f:\n    config = json.load(f)\n\n# Check the full structure to find where capability-evolver is\ndef find_key(obj, key, path=''):\n    if isinstance(obj, dict):\n        for k, v in obj.items():\n            if k == key:\n                print(f'Found at: {path}.{k}')\n                print(f'Value: {v}')\n                return\n            find_key(v, key, f'{path}.{k}')\n    elif isinstance(obj, list):\n        for i, item in enumerate(obj):\n            find_key(item, key, f'{path}[{i}]')\n\nfind_key(config, 'capability-evolver')\n\"","timeout":5}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":10685,"output":364,"cacheRead":26290,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":37339,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":177