{"type":"message","id":"ecbc360f","parentId":"bbcc9068","timestamp":"2026-05-18T07:04:33.774Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"It's disabled. But the user is saying they're still getting the messages. This is a feishu direct message, so it could be:\n1. The messages were sent before the restart and are just now arriving\n2. There's another source of these messages\n3. The session that sent these messages is different\n\nLet me check if the message is from the same session. The user is replying to a specific message about \"Capability Evolver 完成（exit 0）\". But the previous messages I received were also about the same thing. \n\nWait - the user sent the same message twice (same message_id `om_x100b6f9f0fcb4ce8c4c29cd74d99439`). \n\nLooking at the inbox, both messages have the same ID but they're separated by a new message ID, which suggests they're actually from different sessions even though they appear to be replies to the same thing.\n\nThe capability-evolver is now disabled in config, but I should check the logs to see if there's another cron job or scheduled task that's still triggering these messages, or if they're coming from a different source entirely.\n","thinkingSignature":"2eeef0b66f50715233f99ad1f1e41d574792c1771be06f63c53b5f7e85377822"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_m8bipdmjf352_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"tail -100 /tmp/openclaw/openclaw-$(date +%Y-%m-%d).log 2>/dev/null | grep -i \"capability\\|evolver\\|feishu.*send\" | tail -20","timeout":5}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":1253,"output":310,"cacheRead":34883,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":36446,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1779087855505,"responseId":"0659ecf0f9ff0895ba3ff272198ee466"}}
