{"type":"message","id":"4f2c82d8","parentId":"061e5dd2","timestamp":"2026-05-18T07:04:47.910Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The log shows multiple attempts to patch the config, but the capability-evolver was found at `skills.entries.capability-evolver` not `plugins.entries.capability-evolver`. I fixed it in skills.entries and restarted. But the user is still getting messages. \n\nWait - the user sent a \"啥情况\" which means \"what's going on\". This is the same \"🧬 Capability Evolver 完成\" message. It's still coming!\n\nThe capability-evolver is at skills.entries. I already set it to false. But maybe the log shows these are old messages from before my fix. Let me check if the message is still happening after my restart.\n\nActually, looking at the user's message - they're replying to the \"Capability Evolver 完成\" message. \n\nSo the user's asking \"啥情况\" - what's the situation - about getting this message. I need to figure out if it's still coming in after my fix. Let me check if the Gateway is actually up and responding to commands, and whether the config change I made to skills.entries.capability-evolver.enabled = false actually took effect.\n","thinkingSignature":"ffaefa9bb196254af4c727d49a53612fd3881a96c99c332dcc94863cc1c61855"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_2ks467bbi980_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"curl -s http://127.0.0.1:18789/api/status 2>/dev/null | python3 -m json.tool 2>/dev/null | head -30","timeout":5}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":2619,"output":293,"cacheRead":34906,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":37818,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1779087873897,"responseId":"0659ed021b6c6100cc99b50dcc5af429"}}
