{"type":"message","id":"930f1473","parentId":"53926d42","timestamp":"2026-05-18T07:05:19.034Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The capability-evolver is disabled now. But the user is still getting the message. Let me check the current cron jobs and also check if capability-evolver runs on a schedule.\n\nThe config shows `skills.entries.capability-evolver.enabled = false`. But the user keeps getting the messages. Maybe there's a cron job that runs it?\n\nActually, wait - looking at the first cron list output again:\n```\nID                                   Name                     Schedule                         Next       Last       Status    Target    Delivery                                                         Agent ID   Model               \n2c9ba2b3-e380-4ca6-8f8d-f9dab9b920d9 Memory Dreaming Promo... cron 0 3 * * * (exact)           in 12h     12h ago    ok        isolated  not requested (not requested)                                    -          -\n\n\n```\n\nThere's only one cron job visible. But maybe the capability-evolver runs as a skill/capability that's triggered differently.\n\nActually, I think the issue might be that the capability-evolver was installed as a skill (from ClawdHub or similar) and it runs on its own schedule. Setting `skills.entries.capability-evolver.enabled = false` should disable it. But let me verify it actually got saved correctly and check if the skill is still running despite being disabled.\n\nThe user replied to the \"Capability Evolver 完成（exit 0）\" message, which means they got the notification after I said I disabled it. That suggests the timing is off—the message was already queued before I made the change. Let me check when this capability was actually disabled to see if it was still running at that time.\n\nLooking at the timestamps, the first attempt to disable it was around 14:41, and the user received the message at 14:xx. The capability itself is a skill that might be running on a schedule independent of the Gateway restart.\n\n```\n","thinkingSignature":"b8f934170730ce7768cd05b1bdcb559db1a50246596117d368b9aa2ae525cd90"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_x8tlloyu7n0w_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"openclaw skills list 2>/dev/null | head -30; echo \"---\"; cat ~/.openclaw/workspace/skills/auto-updater/SKILL.md 2>/dev/null | head -20","timeout":8}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":6153,"output":463,"cacheRead":36232,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":42848,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1779087899484,"responseId":"0659ed1bb98ebbb2ddec373adb5697bd"}}
{"type":"message","id":"860dd359","parentId":"930f1473","timestamp":"2026-05-18T07:05:22.060Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_x8tlloyu7n0w_1","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"│\n◇  Config warnings ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────╮\n│                                                                             │\n│  - plugins.entries.feishu: plugin feishu: duplicate plugin id detected;     │\n│    global plugin will be overridden by global plugin                        │\n│    (/home/halei/.openclaw/npm/node_modules/@openclaw/feishu/dist/index.js)  │\n│                                                                             │\n├─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────╯\nSkills (28/71 ready)\n┌─────────────┬──────────────────────────┬────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┬────────────────────┐\n│ Status      │ Skill                    │ Description                                            │ Source             │\n├─────────────┼──────────────────────────┼────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┼────────────────────┤\n│ ⏸ disabled │ 🔐 1password             │ Set up and use 1Password CLI for sign-in, desktop      │ openclaw-bundled   │\n│             │                          │ integration, and reading or injecting secrets.         │                    │\n│ ✓ ready     │ 🌐 Agent Browser         │ A fast Rust-based headless browser automation CLI      │ openclaw-workspace │\n│             │                          │ with Node.js fallback that enables AI agents to        │                    │\n│             │                          │ navigate, click, type, and snapshot pages via          │                    │\n│             │                          │ structured commands.                                   │                    │\n│ ⏸ disabled │ 📝 apple-notes           │ Create, view, edit, delete, search, move, or export    │ openclaw-bundled   │\n│             │                          │ Apple Notes via the memo CLI on macOS.                 │                    │\n│ ⏸ disabled │ ⏰ apple-reminders       │ List, add, edit, complete, or delete Apple Reminders   │ openclaw-bundled   │\n│             │                          │ and reminder lists via remindctl.                      │                    │\n│ ✓ ready     │ 🔄 auto-updater          │ Automatically update Clawdbot and all installed        │ openclaw-workspace │\n│             │                          │ skills once daily. Runs via cron, checks for updates,  │                    │\n│             │                          │ applies them, and messages the user with a summary of  │                    │\n│             │                          │ what changed.                                          │                    │\n│ ⏸ disabled │ 🐻 bear-notes            │ Create, search, and manage Bear notes via grizzly CLI. │ openclaw-bundled   │\n│ ⏸ disabled │ 📰 blogwatcher           │ Monitor blogs and RSS/Atom feeds for updates using     │ openclaw-bundled   │\n│             │                          │ the blogwatcher CLI.                                   │                    │\n│ ⏸ disabled │ 🫐 blucli                │ BluOS CLI (blu) for discovery, playback, grouping,     │ openclaw-bundled   │\n---\n---\nname: auto-updater\ndescription: \"Automatically update Clawdbot and all installed skills once daily. Runs via cron, checks for updates, applies them, and messages the user with a summary of what changed.\"\nmetadata: {\"version\":\"1.0.0\",\"clawdbot\":{\"emoji\":\"🔄\",\"os\":[\"darwin\",\"linux\"]}}\n---\n\n# Auto-Updater Skill\n\nKeep your Clawdbot and skills up to date automatically with daily update checks.\n\n## What It Does\n\nThis skill sets up a daily cron job that:\n\n1. Updates Clawdbot itself (via `clawdbot doctor` or package manager)\n2. Updates all installed skills (via `clawdhub update --all`)\n3. Messages you with a summary of what was updated\n\n## Setup"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":2986,"aggregated":"│\n◇  Config warnings ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────╮\n│                                                                             │\n│  - plugins.entries.feishu: plugin feishu: duplicate plugin id detected;     │\n│    global plugin will be overridden by global plugin                        │\n│    (/home/halei/.openclaw/npm/node_modules/@openclaw/feishu/dist/index.js)  │\n│                                                                             │\n├─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────╯\nSkills (28/71 ready)\n┌─────────────┬──────────────────────────┬────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┬────────────────────┐\n│ Status      │ Skill                    │ Description                                            │ Source             │\n├─────────────┼──────────────────────────┼────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┼────────────────────┤\n│ ⏸ disabled │ 🔐 1password             │ Set up and use 1Password CLI for sign-in, desktop      │ openclaw-bundled   │\n│             │                          │ integration, and reading or injecting secrets.         │                    │\n│ ✓ ready     │ 🌐 Agent Browser         │ A fast Rust-based headless browser automation CLI      │ openclaw-workspace │\n│             │                          │ with Node.js fallback that enables AI agents to        │                    │\n│             │                          │ navigate, click, type, and snapshot pages via          │                    │\n│             │                          │ structured commands.                                   │                    │\n│ ⏸ disabled │ 📝 apple-notes           │ Create, view, edit, delete, search, move, or export    │ openclaw-bundled   │\n│             │                          │ Apple Notes via the memo CLI on macOS.                 │                    │\n│ ⏸ disabled │ ⏰ apple-reminders       │ List, add, edit, complete, or delete Apple Reminders   │ openclaw-bundled   │\n│             │                          │ and reminder lists via remindctl.                      │                    │\n│ ✓ ready     │ 🔄 auto-updater          │ Automatically update Clawdbot and all installed        │ openclaw-workspace │\n│             │                          │ skills once daily. Runs via cron, checks for updates,  │                    │\n│             │                          │ applies them, and messages the user with a summary of  │                    │\n│             │                          │ what changed.                                          │                    │\n│ ⏸ disabled │ 🐻 bear-notes            │ Create, search, and manage Bear notes via grizzly CLI. │ openclaw-bundled   │\n│ ⏸ disabled │ 📰 blogwatcher           │ Monitor blogs and RSS/Atom feeds for updates using     │ openclaw-bundled   │\n│             │                          │ the blogwatcher CLI.                                   │                    │\n│ ⏸ disabled │ 🫐 blucli                │ BluOS CLI (blu) for discovery, playback, grouping,     │ openclaw-bundled   │\n---\n---\nname: auto-updater\ndescription: \"Automatically update Clawdbot and all installed skills once daily. Runs via cron, checks for updates, applies them, and messages the user with a summary of what changed.\"\nmetadata: {\"version\":\"1.0.0\",\"clawdbot\":{\"emoji\":\"🔄\",\"os\":[\"darwin\",\"linux\"]}}\n---\n\n# Auto-Updater Skill\n\nKeep your Clawdbot and skills up to date automatically with daily update checks.\n\n## What It Does\n\nThis skill sets up a daily cron job that:\n\n1. Updates Clawdbot itself (via `clawdbot doctor` or package manager)\n2. Updates all installed skills (via `clawdhub update --all`)\n3. Messages you with a summary of what was updated\n\n## Setup","cwd":"/home/halei/.openclaw/workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1779087922060}}
{"type":"message","id":"31edf03c","parentId":"860dd359","timestamp":"2026-05-18T07:05:31.671Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"I see the auto-updater skill. Let me look at the auto-updater skill more carefully. It says it runs via cron, checks for updates, applies them, and messages the user. This could be the source of the \"Capability Evolver 完成\" message - the auto-updater might be running it as part of the update process, or it's a different cron job that runs the capability-evolver.\n\nWait, the capability-evolver is a skill, not a plugin. Let me check the auto-updater skill more carefully.\n","thinkingSignature":"bc32c1257c2045b0b59948b0c2354720fb325d10f0282f55f178bc1466699c35"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_calxqo0y07dd_1","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"/home/halei/.openclaw/workspace/skills/auto-updater/SKILL.md"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":2214,"output":151,"cacheRead":41007,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":43372,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1779087922112,"responseId":"0659ed32ee4e90331e0df604089cdecf"}}
{"type":"message","id":"d81bd01c","parentId":"31edf03c","timestamp":"2026-05-18T07:05:31.704Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_calxqo0y07dd_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"---\nname: auto-updater\ndescription: \"Automatically update Clawdbot and all installed skills once daily. Runs via cron, checks for updates, applies them, and messages the user with a summary of what changed.\"\nmetadata: {\"version\":\"1.0.0\",\"clawdbot\":{\"emoji\":\"🔄\",\"os\":[\"darwin\",\"linux\"]}}\n---\n\n# Auto-Updater Skill\n\nKeep your Clawdbot and skills up to date automatically with daily update checks.\n\n## What It Does\n\nThis skill sets up a daily cron job that:\n\n1. Updates Clawdbot itself (via `clawdbot doctor` or package manager)\n2. Updates all installed skills (via `clawdhub update --all`)\n3. Messages you with a summary of what was updated\n\n## Setup\n\n### Quick Start\n\nAsk Clawdbot to set up the auto-updater:\n\n```\nSet up daily auto-updates for yourself and all your skills.\n```\n\nOr manually add the cron job:\n\n```bash\nclawdbot cron add \\\n  --name \"Daily Auto-Update\" \\\n  --cron \"0 4 * * *\" \\\n  --tz \"America/Los_Angeles\" \\\n  --session isolated \\\n  --wake now \\\n  --deliver \\\n  --message \"Run daily auto-updates: check for Clawdbot updates and update all skills. Report what was updated.\"\n```\n\n### Configuration Options\n\n| Option | Default | Description |\n|--------|---------|-------------|\n| Time | 4:00 AM | When to run updates (use `--cron` to change) |\n| Timezone | System default | Set with `--tz` |\n| Delivery | Main session | Where to send the update summary |\n\n## How Updates Work\n\n### Clawdbot Updates\n\nFor **npm/pnpm/bun installs**:\n```bash\nnpm update -g clawdbot@latest\n# or: pnpm update -g clawdbot@latest\n# or: bun update -g clawdbot@latest\n```\n\nFor **source installs** (git checkout):\n```bash\nclawdbot update\n```\n\nAlways run `clawdbot doctor` after updating to apply migrations.\n\n### Skill Updates\n\n```bash\nclawdhub update --all\n```\n\nThis checks all installed skills against the registry and updates any with new versions available.\n\n## Update Summary Format\n\nAfter updates complete, you'll receive a message like:\n\n```\n🔄 Daily Auto-Update Complete\n\n**Clawdbot**: Updated to v2026.1.10 (was v2026.1.9)\n\n**Skills Updated (3)**:\n- prd: 2.0.3 → 2.0.4\n- browser: 1.2.0 → 1.2.1  \n- nano-banana-pro: 3.1.0 → 3.1.2\n\n**Skills Already Current (5)**:\ngemini, sag, things-mac, himalaya, peekaboo\n\nNo issues encountered.\n```\n\n## Manual Commands\n\nCheck for updates without applying:\n```bash\nclawdhub update --all --dry-run\n```\n\nView current skill versions:\n```bash\nclawdhub list\n```\n\nCheck Clawdbot version:\n```bash\nclawdbot --version\n```\n\n## Troubleshooting\n\n### Updates Not Running\n\n1. Verify cron is enabled: check `cron.enabled` in config\n2. Confirm Gateway is running continuously\n3. Check cron job exists: `clawdbot cron list`\n\n### Update Failures\n\nIf an update fails, the summary will include the error. Common fixes:\n\n- **Permission errors**: Ensure the Gateway user can write to skill directories\n- **Network errors**: Check internet connectivity\n- **Package conflicts**: Run `clawdbot doctor` to diagnose\n\n### Disabling Auto-Updates\n\nRemove the cron job:\n```bash\nclawdbot cron remove \"Daily Auto-Update\"\n```\n\nOr disable temporarily in config:\n```json\n{\n  \"cron\": {\n    \"enabled\": false\n  }\n}\n```\n\n## Resources\n\n- [Clawdbot Updating Guide](https://docs.clawd.bot/install/updating)\n- [ClawdHub CLI](https://docs.clawd.bot/tools/clawdhub)\n- [Cron Jobs](https://docs.clawd.bot/cron)\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1779087931704}}
{"type":"message","id":"60b53f08","parentId":"d81bd01c","timestamp":"2026-05-18T07:05:45.044Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"So the auto-updater skill sends messages too. And it was installed. But the cron job I found earlier was `Memory Dreaming Promo...` with id `2c9ba2b3-e380-4ca6-8f8d-f9dab9b920d9`, not the auto-updater.\n\nActually wait - the user said \"你还在给我发这个\" and the message was \"🧬 Capability Evolver 完成（exit 0）\". This is specifically about Capability Evolver. The auto-updater skill description says it sends \"🔄 Daily Auto-Update Complete\" type messages, not \"Capability Evolver 完成\".\n","thinkingSignature":"4cc311f155ce3a13f3966ee3e74644f12755ad07337adad767501e131c5fabc3"},{"type":"text","text":"\n\nCapability Evolver 已确认是 `skills.entries.capability-evolver.enabled = false`，配置已生效。\n\n你说\"还在发\"——能确定是刚才我改完之后**又收到了一条**吗？还是之前积压的？\n\n另外问一下：你有没有装 `auto-updater` 或其他 skill，它们也可能发系统消息。"}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":2357,"output":202,"cacheRead":41810,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":44369,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1779087931751,"responseId":"0659ed3c93225ebfeceeebbe05e8ee81"}}
