{"type":"message","id":"c765f351","parentId":"0acf0419","timestamp":"2026-05-18T07:06:57.341Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user is pointing out that I should be able to see the messages I'm sending - they're referring to the capability evolver completion messages that I (KIIT/the main agent session) am apparently sending. The user is saying \"the messages you're sending to me, you can see them too right?\" - implying I should know what message they're talking about since I'm the one sending it.\n\nWait - but I don't think I'm the one sending \"🧬 Capability Evolver 完成（exit 0）\". That seems like a system message from a plugin/skill called \"Capability Evolver\", not a message from the KIIT agent itself.\n\nBut the user is saying I can see the messages I'm sending. Maybe they're referring to the fact that in this Feishu conversation, the messages I send appear here too. So the user is essentially saying \"you sent me this message, you should be able to see it in the conversation too.\"\n\nBut the message \"🧬 Capability Evolver 完成（exit 0）\" doesn't appear in my conversation history above. It must be a message that the system/plugin sent directly to the user, not through my session.\n\nHmm, let me think about this differently. The user seems to be getting these messages. The capability-evolver skill/plugin sends completion notifications. I disabled it. But the user is still getting them...\n\nWait - when did the user last receive this message? If it was after my config change, then something is wrong. If it was before, then it's just backlog.\n\nActually, the user's latest message \"你发给我的信息，你能看到呀\" - they're pointing out that I should see the messages that I'm sending. Maybe they're showing me the message again? The message_id is om_x100b6f9fe81558c8c3c246afca1f2b6 which is different from the previous one (om_x100b6f9fd33ea054c3c15e8cb8e243f).\n\n\nThis is a new message in the thread with a different message_id, so the user is sending a fresh message now rather than it being the same notification. They're likely continuing to complain about these messages or showing me another instance of them.\n\nThe user is saying \"you can see the messages you send to me\" - which is strange because \"Capability Evolver 完成\" doesn't appear in my conversation context. This suggests either the message was deleted from my context but not from theirs, or the Capability Evolver plugin is sending these notifications directly through Feishu outside of my conversation. The capability-evolver skill seems to be sending these notifications directly to the user via the Feishu channel, bypassing my conversation entirely. This would explain why I can't see them in my own context - they're being delivered as system notifications from the plugin itself rather than messages within our conversation thread.\n","thinkingSignature":"bd8d2c7b7c78b6c3b2386b1a60a0345bb4045a9fa38dc98dc48d658ed42e14af"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_8tc0ox6v0zig_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"find ~/.openclaw/workspace/skills -name \"*.md\" 2>/dev/null | xargs grep -l -i \"capability.*evolver\\|evolver\" 2>/dev/null | head -5","timeout":5}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":1936,"output":654,"cacheRead":42755,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":45345,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1779087984484,"responseId":"0659ed70ede5dd6b2490f0ccbb11f097"}}
