{"type":"message","id":"ac52dcb4","parentId":"528510a5","timestamp":"2026-05-18T07:15:39.893Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"So the agents don't have their own workspace subdirectories. The workspace directories at the top level are:\n- `~/.openclaw/workspace/` - the main workspace\n- `~/.openclaw/workspace-archive-e-commerce/` - an archived workspace\n\nAnd from the backup script, it already backs up:\n- `workspace/` → `workspace/`\n- `workspace-main/` → `workspace-main/`\n\nSo there are only two workspace directories that are backed up. The user said \"每个agent的workspace\" but actually each agent uses the shared `~/.openclaw/workspace/` directory (except tts which has its own `workspace-tts/`). Let me check the openclaw config to confirm the workspace settings for each agent.\n","thinkingSignature":"334718c8323a61540372a1a68a9bff98948dffcc030d753f6e78b3b68513ba02"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_b2w0svtaf98c_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"python3 -c \"\nimport json\nwith open('/home/halei/.openclaw/openclaw.json', 'r') as f:\n    config = json.load(f)\nfor agent in config.get('agents', {}).get('list', []):\n    aid = agent.get('id')\n    ws = agent.get('workspace', 'inherited')\n    print(f'{aid}: workspace={ws}')\n\"","timeout":5}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":1876,"output":262,"cacheRead":50337,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":52475,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1779088525437,"responseId":"0659ef8eab87871118f5e4dfe1622f05"}}
