{"type":"message","id":"726df3a6","parentId":"f26b27c3","timestamp":"2026-05-18T09:19:12.635Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_m00rsdp6617l_1","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"=== director ===\n_你不是一个聊天机器人。你正在成为一个存在。_\n\n## 核心真理\n---\n=== ops ===\n_你不是一个聊天机器人。你正在成为一个存在。_\n\n## 核心真理\n---\n=== finance ===\n_你不是一个聊天机器人。你正在成为一个存在。_\n\n## 核心真理\n---\n=== review ===\n_你不是一个聊天机器人。你正在成为一个存在。_\n\n## 核心真理\n---"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":46,"aggregated":"=== director ===\n_你不是一个聊天机器人。你正在成为一个存在。_\n\n## 核心真理\n---\n=== ops ===\n_你不是一个聊天机器人。你正在成为一个存在。_\n\n## 核心真理\n---\n=== finance ===\n_你不是一个聊天机器人。你正在成为一个存在。_\n\n## 核心真理\n---\n=== review ===\n_你不是一个聊天机器人。你正在成为一个存在。_\n\n## 核心真理\n---","cwd":"/home/halei/.openclaw/workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1779095952634}}
{"type":"message","id":"9bc4fe6e","parentId":"726df3a6","timestamp":"2026-05-18T09:19:29.242Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"All the SOUL.md files appear to be the same generic template. None of the agents have specific SOUL.md content - they're all using the same generic template.\n\nNow let me think about whether the current team structure makes sense for \"TK 跨境电商团队\" (TK Cross-border E-commerce Team).\n\nCurrent agents:\n1. **KITT-AGI** (main) - 大管家，多Agent协调\n2. **TK 选品大师** (tts) - 选品\n3. **Agent 编排工程师** (agent-orchestrator) - Agent编排\n\n\n4. **TK 内容专家** (content) - 内容创作\n5. **TK 达人专家** (koc) - KOC/达人运营\n6. **TK 投流专家** (traffic) - 流量投放\n7. **TK 运营助手** (ops) - 运营辅助\n8. **TK 运营总监** (director) - 运营总监\n9. **finance** - 财务（未命名，无workspace）\n10. **TK 客服专家** (review) - 客服\n\nThe structure covers product selection, content creation, creator partnerships, traffic acquisition, operations support, and customer service, but there's no dedicated finance agent and the workflow between agents appears disorganized. The real problem is that the orchestrator and director roles seem redundant—orchestration could be embedded directly into the director role rather than existing as a separate agent.\n","thinkingSignature":"eee7f6c4a0bf7b95a14fc2357211fc62a3409f0b9fe91e8f1772505ebc432ff8"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_e5ogvwi8g7jz_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"ls ~/workspace-finance/ 2>/dev/null; echo \"---\"; ls ~/workspace-review/ 2>/dev/null | head -10","timeout":5}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":2062,"output":364,"cacheRead":57788,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":60214,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1779095952732,"responseId":"065a0c913082d8b3d6163e26fdaa327f"}}
{"type":"message","id":"5c46ea6c","parentId":"9bc4fe6e","timestamp":"2026-05-18T09:19:29.311Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_e5ogvwi8g7jz_1","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"AGENTS.md\nDREAMS.md\nHEARTBEAT.md\nIDENTITY.md\nmemory\nSOUL.md\nTOOLS.md\nUSER.md\n---\nAGENTS.md\nDREAMS.md\nHEARTBEAT.md\nIDENTITY.md\nmemory\nSOUL.md\nTOOLS.md\nUSER.md"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":31,"aggregated":"AGENTS.md\nDREAMS.md\nHEARTBEAT.md\nIDENTITY.md\nmemory\nSOUL.md\nTOOLS.md\nUSER.md\n---\nAGENTS.md\nDREAMS.md\nHEARTBEAT.md\nIDENTITY.md\nmemory\nSOUL.md\nTOOLS.md\nUSER.md","cwd":"/home/halei/.openclaw/workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1779095969311}}
{"type":"message","id":"c49987f5","parentId":"5c46ea6c","timestamp":"2026-05-18T09:20:05.386Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now let me think about this from first principles. What's the actual TK e-commerce team structure that makes sense for TikTok Shop?\n\nThe user is running a TikTok e-commerce business (TK = TikTok). They need:\n1. **选品 (Product Selection)** - Finding what to sell\n2. **内容 (Content)** - Creating content to promote products\n3. **达人 (KOC/KOL)** - Managing influencer relationships\n4. **投流 (Traffic)** - Running ads\n5. **运营 (Operations)** - Day-to-day ops support\n6. **客服 (Customer Service)** - Handling customer issues\n7. **财务 (Finance)** - Financial tracking/analysis\n\n\n8. **运营总监 (Director)** - Oversight/coordinator\n\nThe real issue is that a \"Director\" agent without clearly defined authority won't work in practice—it'll either duplicate what the main KIIT agent does or sit idle. In a small TikTok Shop business, traditional organizational hierarchy doesn't map well onto AI agents. I should think about what's actually necessary: core operations like product selection, content, KOC management, and traffic are essential, while a dedicated director role might just add unnecessary overhead.\n\nThe more I consider this, the clearer it becomes that the director agent is redundant when I already have KIIT as the main orchestrator. For a lean e-commerce operation, I probably only need 4-5 specialized roles rather than 8+. And finance is questionable too—basic bookkeeping doesn't need its own agent when KIIT can handle that. Let me map out a minimal viable team structure that actually makes sense for the workload.\n\nActually, stepping back—I'm overthinking this. The real question is whether these agents are actually doing useful work or just existing. The director agent especially feels like unnecessary overhead if KIIT is already coordinating everything. I should give the user a straightforward recommendation: drop the director, keep the specialists that are actively being used, and make sure each one has clear, specific responsibilities rather than vague managerial titles.\n","thinkingSignature":"237f150f9d5af798ce046b66b20036850507b263bf9f56fd7a7d6ee7e4ec895c"},{"type":"text","text":"\n\n坦白说，我觉得这个团队配置有问题。让我直接说：\n\n**当前 10 个 agent：**\n`main` · `tts` · `agent-orchestrator` · `content` · `koc` · `traffic` · `ops` · `director` · `finance` · `review`\n\n**主要问题：**\n\n**1. `director`（运营总监）— 重复且多余**\n你已经有了 `main`（KIIT 大总管）做全局协调。运营总监这个角色在 AI agent 团队里很尴尬——它没有实权（不能直接指挥其他 agent），又没有独立执行能力。如果 TK 遇到问题，应该找大总管协调，而不是一个\"运营总监\" agent。这层管理是给人设计的，不是给 AI 设计的。\n\n**2. `ops`（运营助手）— 边界模糊**\nops 是打杂的，但其他每个 agent 本身就已经很专业了。\"运营助手\"在这个架构里不知道该干什么，容易变成一个什么都沾但什么都不精的空壳。\n\n**3. `agent-orchestrator` — 同样是重复**\n你已经有了 KIIT 做编排，再来一个\"编排工程师\" agent 完全是重复职能。\n\n**4. `finance` — 没有独立存在的必要**\n财务分析/账务管理这些，KIIT 完全能cover，不需要单独一个 agent。\n\n**5. `review`（客服）— 方向存疑**\nTikTok Shop 的客服需要实时响应买家消息，agent 的响应速度够吗？这个角色更像是需要集成到客服系统里，而不是一个飞书 bot。\n\n---\n\n**建议的精简方向：**\n\n| 保留 | 理由 |\n|------|------|\n| `tts`（选品） | 核心专业能力 |\n| `content`（内容） | 核心专业能力 |\n| `koc`（达人） | 核心专业能力 |\n| `traffic`（投流） | 核心专业能力 |\n| `main`（大总管） | 全局协调，唯一入口 |\n\n| 建议删除/合并 | 理由 |\n|---------------|------|\n| `director` | 和 main 重复 |\n| `agent-orchestrator` | 和 main 重复 |\n| `ops` | 边界模糊，可被 main 吸收 |\n| `finance` | 可由 main 代管 |\n| `review` | 需要实时性，不适合 agent |\n\n你觉得呢？要按这个方向精简吗？"}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":2016,"output":907,"cacheRead":57976,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":60899,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1779095969400,"responseId":"065a0ca1be61442eb775f29aaec96b2d"}}
{"type":"message","id":"ca9eec5a","parentId":"c49987f5","timestamp":"2026-05-18T09:25:19.527Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[message_id: om_x100b6f99e11df084c4c704fe74391c9]\nou_f590c429b7ded95568bebca2f534efdb: 运营总监负责制定运营方向和总体运营。\n\n具体的工作内容包括：\n1. 类目管理：在东南亚飞跃新马泰地区，管理5个站点。\n2. 数据分析：每个站点的数据都要合并汇总分析。\n3. 运营助手：负责提报和检查一些活动"}],"timestamp":1779096319514}}
{"type":"custom_message","customType":"openclaw.runtime-context","content":"Conversation info (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"chat_id\": \"user:ou_f590c429b7ded95568bebca2f534efdb\",\n  \"message_id\": \"om_x100b6f99e11df084c4c704fe74391c9\",\n  \"sender_id\": \"ou_f590c429b7ded95568bebca2f534efdb\",\n  \"sender\": \"ou_f590c429b7ded95568bebca2f534efdb\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"Mon 2026-05-18 17:25 GMT+8\"\n}\n```\n\nSender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"ou_f590c429b7ded95568bebca2f534efdb\",\n  \"id\": \"ou_f590c429b7ded95568bebca2f534efdb\",\n  \"name\": \"ou_f590c429b7ded95568bebca2f534efdb\"\n}\n```","display":false,"details":{"source":"openclaw-runtime-context"},"id":"13a098b7","parentId":"ca9eec5a","timestamp":"2026-05-18T09:25:19.527Z"}
{"type":"message","id":"d7815542","parentId":"13a098b7","timestamp":"2026-05-18T09:25:56.727Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user is explaining what the 运营总监 (director) actually does. It seems like the director role does have specific responsibilities:\n\n1. Category management: managing 5 sites across Southeast Asia (Singapore, Malaysia, Thailand - the \"新马泰\" region)\n2. Data analysis: consolidating and analyzing data from all sites\n3. Ops assistant: handling activity registration and checks\n\nSo the director isn't just a coordinator - it has specific data aggregation and management responsibilities. This is different from what I thought.\n\nLet me reconsider. Maybe the director IS useful if it:\n- Aggregates data from all 5 sites and provides unified analysis\n- Manages category strategy across markets\n- Coordinates with ops for activity execution\n\n\n- Has clear responsibilities that are actually meaningful\n\nAnd the 运营助手 (ops) could be the execution arm of the director - doing the ground work like activity registration and checking, while the director handles planning and analysis. Though the fact that ops is its own agent separate from director is a bit odd since director would naturally delegate to it.\n\nLooking at the main agent (KIIT) which coordinates the overall multi-agent system, and the director which has specialized responsibilities in category management, data aggregation, and operational support across the 5 sites - these actually feel distinct. The question is whether both roles justify separate agent status or if they're better merged.\n\nThe ops agent probably shouldn't exist as its own standalone entity if it's really just the director's execution arm. The real issue is that without proper inter-agent communication protocols, the director and ops would just be isolated bots that don't actually coordinate with each other the way they should.\n","thinkingSignature":"70764acb122cc9c8b8631f2ef9cb7641b07cba094b20a8bdec4ee8bd48c66730"},{"type":"text","text":"\n\n明白了，那运营总监的职责其实很具体——不是管理层级的重复，而是有实质内容的。\n\n让我重新梳理一下：\n\n| Agent | 职责 | 是否有实质内容 |\n|-------|------|--------------|\n| `director` | 类目管理（5站点）、数据汇总分析、运营规划 | ✅ 有 |\n| `ops` | 负责提报和检查活动（听 director 指挥） | ⚠️ 方向对，但执行有问题 |\n\n**核心问题不在于 director 是否有必要，而在于：**\n\n**1. `director` 和 `ops` 之间的协作没有打通**\n`ops` 是听 director 指挥的执行层，但这两个 agent 之间目前是**没有联动机制**的——它们各自独立响应用户，不知道谁该向谁汇报。如果 director 说\"今天提报这个活动\"，ops 不会自动收到这个指令。\n\n**2. `director` 的数据分析依赖数据源**\n5个站点的数据要合并汇总——这些数据从哪里来？目前有没有对接 TikTok Shop 的数据 API？还是靠人工录入？如果数据源没打通，director 只能做定性分析，无法做定量汇总。\n\n**3. `ops` agent 如果没有独立价值，可以精简**\n如果 ops 的工作就是帮 director 提报活动、检查核销，那它其实更像是 director 的一个工具函数，而不是独立 agent。可以把\"活动提报\"这类任务做成 director 的一个执行动作，而不是单独一个 agent。\n\n---\n\n**我的建议：**\n\n先确认几个问题：\n1. 5个站点的数据，现在是怎么汇聚的？有 API 对接还是人工整理？\n2. 运营总监和运营助手之间，你希望它们怎么配合？\n\n搞清楚这两个之后，可以设计一套合理的 agent 协作流程，比如：\n- `director` 负责任务规划和数据分析 → 下达指令给 `ops`\n- `ops` 接收指令执行（活动提报等）→ 汇报结果给 `director`\n\n要不要先把数据源的问题理清楚？"}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":36920,"output":726,"cacheRead":24089,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":61735,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1779096319626,"responseId":"065a0e005ff2f9efb07593e43bf561f5"}}
{"type":"message","id":"9426fd69","parentId":"d7815542","timestamp":"2026-05-18T09:26:00.020Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[message_id: om_x100b6f99fe164898c45987a3dfc5787]\nou_f590c429b7ded95568bebca2f534efdb: 然后客服是必须得要的呀。\n\n那有人在线咨询的时候，还有客服要处理评价里边的这些内容，他也要回复啊"}],"timestamp":1779096360007}}
{"type":"custom_message","customType":"openclaw.runtime-context","content":"Conversation info (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"chat_id\": \"user:ou_f590c429b7ded95568bebca2f534efdb\",\n  \"message_id\": \"om_x100b6f99fe164898c45987a3dfc5787\",\n  \"sender_id\": \"ou_f590c429b7ded95568bebca2f534efdb\",\n  \"sender\": \"ou_f590c429b7ded95568bebca2f534efdb\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"Mon 2026-05-18 17:25 GMT+8\"\n}\n```\n\nSender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"ou_f590c429b7ded95568bebca2f534efdb\",\n  \"id\": \"ou_f590c429b7ded95568bebca2f534efdb\",\n  \"name\": \"ou_f590c429b7ded95568bebca2f534efdb\"\n}\n```","display":false,"details":{"source":"openclaw-runtime-context"},"id":"0ad2af72","parentId":"9426fd69","timestamp":"2026-05-18T09:26:00.020Z"}
{"type":"message","id":"48765fe2","parentId":"0ad2af72","timestamp":"2026-05-18T09:26:32.714Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user is explaining that the 客服 (review/customer service) agent is necessary because:\n1. Real-time online customer consultation\n2. Processing and responding to reviews/testimonials\n\nThis makes sense for a TikTok Shop. Let me think about this differently.\n\nThe challenge with 客服 (customer service) as an AI agent:\n- Customer service needs **real-time responsiveness** - customers expect instant responses on TikTok Shop\n- AI agents are not real-time by default - they're request-response based\n- If a customer sends a message on TikTok Shop, the agent needs to receive that message and respond within seconds/minutes, not in a cron job\n\nBut wait - looking at the channel setup, there's a `feishu` channel. \n\nI'm wondering if customer messages from TikTok Shop are actually routed through Feishu to the agent, or if the feishu account is just being used for internal team communication rather than customer-facing support. The user might be using a bot account for internal coordination, but actual customer service on TikTok Shop could be handled separately through the platform's native messaging system or a different integration altogether.\n\nThe core distinction I'm realizing is that there are really two different operational modes here: proactive (the agent reaches out on a schedule like daily data reports) and reactive (the agent responds when someone messages in). Customer service fundamentally needs to be reactive, so the question is whether this AI agent setup can actually support that real-time responsiveness, or if it's better suited as a tool that helps the human customer service team work more efficiently rather than handling conversations autonomously. Let me reconsider what the user is actually describing. They're talking about managing customer messages and reviews across TikTok Shop, which does require an agent presence. The key insight is that this agent likely operates through Feishu to communicate with the internal team, relaying customer inquiries and review responses rather than handling them directly on the platform itself.\n","thinkingSignature":"947e94f971f5e55c9f87d6d072b3eac9668c553f71dabb535f8eb767e822f49a"},{"type":"text","text":"\n\n你说得对，客服确实是必须的——TikTok Shop 的在线咨询和评价回复是高频、必须及时响应的场景。\n\n**但有个关键问题需要对齐一下：**\n\n\"在线客服\"这个场景，本质上是**被动响应**的——用户来问，我答；用户留差评，我回。这要求 agent 能：\n1. **实时收消息** → 有人发消息，agent 要秒级收到并响应\n2. **主动发消息** → 回复买家消息，需要在 TikTok Shop 平台上发出\n\n**你现在的 agent 是跑在飞书里的。**\n\n这就有两种可能的使用方式：\n\n**方式 A（推荐）：** 客服 agent 作为\"客服人员的助手\"——买家消息通过其他渠道（TikTok Shop 后台、人工中转等）汇集到飞书，agent 先分析、起草回复、识别问题，再由人工确认发出。agent 做**辅助决策**，人做最终执行。\n\n**方式 B：** agent 直接对接 TikTok Shop API，自动回复买家。但这个实现难度大，且 TikTok Shop 的 API 对自动回复有限制。\n\n---\n\n你们现在是**怎么接买家消息的**？是人工在看 TikTok Shop 后台，然后把需要 agent 协助的内容转发到飞书？还是希望 agent 能直接处理？\n\n搞清楚这个链路，才能判断 agent 该扮演什么角色、以及需不需要在飞书里专门配一个\"客服专家\" agent。"}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":2737,"output":675,"cacheRead":59073,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":62485,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1779096360121,"responseId":"065a0e2810639e1ccf5cae454cd04948"}}
{"type":"message","id":"16f6152e","parentId":"48765fe2","timestamp":"2026-05-18T09:27:21.238Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[message_id: om_x100b6f99f9ae44a0c10716f5510dabf]\nou_f590c429b7ded95568bebca2f534efdb: 我现在有个特别头疼的问题，就是除了这个TK选品大师我现在正在调试，已经配了一些流程以外，其他的都还没弄呢。\n\n就是只是让你调整过一下他们里边的这些内容。文件变为中文，那你先都给他们配置好吧，最起码能让他们先成为一个正常的agent，然后我一个一个的再调呗，你说呢？"}],"timestamp":1779096441227}}
