{"type":"message","id":"e6bd0300","parentId":"4a9b7782","timestamp":"2026-05-18T09:32:28.349Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Conversation info (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"chat_id\": \"user:ou_f590c429b7ded95568bebca2f534efdb\",\n  \"message_id\": \"om_x100b6f99f508e4a8c33cae08160d8ef\",\n  \"sender_id\": \"ou_f590c429b7ded95568bebca2f534efdb\",\n  \"sender\": \"ou_f590c429b7ded95568bebca2f534efdb\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"Mon 2026-05-18 17:28 GMT+8\"\n}\n```\n\nSender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"ou_f590c429b7ded95568bebca2f534efdb\",\n  \"id\": \"ou_f590c429b7ded95568bebca2f534efdb\",\n  \"name\": \"ou_f590c429b7ded95568bebca2f534efdb\"\n}\n```\n\n[message_id: om_x100b6f99f508e4a8c33cae08160d8ef]\nou_f590c429b7ded95568bebca2f534efdb: 现在是这样的，如果都处理TK后台的里边这些业务，我是可以设置一些子账号出来的，是没有问题的。\n\n就是应该还会以浏览器登录为主，所以是不是要用到你，也就是OpenClaw的多浏览器实例，就是独立实例支持，因为我是部署在一个乌班图桌面版的，它们是可以分别调动浏览器的"}],"timestamp":1779096740099}}
{"type":"message","id":"836a0958","parentId":"e6bd0300","timestamp":"2026-05-18T09:32:44.795Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user is explaining their architecture:\n\n1. TikTok Shop backend operations are done via browser logins\n2. They can set up sub-accounts for TikTok Shop (for different agents to use)\n3. They're running OpenClaw on Ubuntu Desktop\n4. They want to use OpenClaw's multi-browser instances so each agent can control its own browser independently\n\nThis is a very sensible architecture! Each agent would log into TikTok Shop's seller backend with its own sub-account credentials, and use a dedicated browser instance to do its work (check orders, respond to customers, manage products, etc.).\n\nOpenClaw does support browser automation with multiple browser profiles/instances. The browser tool can be configured with different profiles. \n\nI should check whether the existing agents actually have the browser tool configured in their profiles, since that's what would enable each one to operate independently in its own browser context.\n","thinkingSignature":"efda5b8ba32ef5556030a7ca4d62464a7d83711a9a086722b47b068d2aced776"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_5u29wug34mmv_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"python3 -c \"\nimport json\nwith open('/home/halei/.openclaw/openclaw.json', 'r') as f:\n    config = json.load(f)\nfor agent in config.get('agents', {}).get('list', []):\n    aid = agent.get('id')\n    tools = agent.get('tools', {})\n    browser_profile = tools.get('browser', {}).get('profile', 'default') if isinstance(tools, dict) else 'not set'\n    print(f\\\"{aid}: tools={list(tools.keys()) if isinstance(tools, dict) else tools}\\\")\n\" 2>/dev/null","timeout":5}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":2821,"output":344,"cacheRead":65533,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":68698,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stop